SIMPLE: penurious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penurious
<hw>Pe*nu"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Penury</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Excessively sparing in the use
of money; sordid; stingy; miserly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>penurious</xex>
niggard of his wealth.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not bountiful or liberal; scanty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here creeps along a poor, <qex>penurious</qex> stream.</q>
<rj><qau>C. Pitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Destitute of money; suffering extreme want.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧My <xex>penurious</xex> band.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Avaricious; covetous; parsimonious; miserly;
niggardly; stingy. See <er>Avaricious</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>--<wordforms><wf>Pe*nu"ri*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pe*nu"ri*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penury</ent>⟦br⟧
